**File-based routing** means folders and files in the `app/` directory automatically create routes.

**1. Static Routes** — Fixed URLs

```
app/
├── page.tsx              → /
├── about/
│   └── page.tsx          → /about
├── contact/
│   └── page.tsx          → /contact
└── blog/
    └── page.tsx          → /blog
```

Example:
```tsx
// app/about/page.tsx
export default function AboutPage() {
  return <h1>About Us</h1>;
}
// Accessible at: /about
```

**2. Dynamic Routes** — Variable segments (use [brackets])

```
app/
└── blog/
    └── [id]/
        └── page.tsx      → /blog/1, /blog/2, /blog/anything
```

Example:
```tsx
// app/blog/[id]/page.tsx
export default function BlogPost({ params }) {
  return <h1>Blog Post: {params.id}</h1>;
}

// /blog/123 → params.id = "123"
// /blog/my-post → params.id = "my-post"
```

**Nested dynamic routes:**
```
app/
└── shop/
    └── [category]/
        └── [product]/
            └── page.tsx  → /shop/electronics/laptop
```

```tsx
// app/shop/[category]/[product]/page.tsx
export default function ProductPage({ params }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Category: {params.category}</p>
      <p>Product: {params.product}</p>
    </div>
  );
}

// /shop/electronics/laptop
// → params = { category: "electronics", product: "laptop" }
```

**3. Catch-All Routes** — Match multiple segments (use [...slug])

```
app/
└── docs/
    └── [...slug]/
        └── page.tsx
```

Example:
```tsx
// app/docs/[...slug]/page.tsx
export default function DocsPage({ params }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Documentation</h1>
      <p>Path: {params.slug.join('/')}</p>
    </div>
  );
}

// /docs/getting-started
// → params.slug = ["getting-started"]

// /docs/api/authentication
// → params.slug = ["api", "authentication"]

// /docs/guides/deployment/vercel
// → params.slug = ["guides", "deployment", "vercel"]
```

**Optional catch-all** — Use [[...slug]] to also match the base route:

```
app/
└── shop/
    └── [[...slug]]/
        └── page.tsx

// Matches:
// /shop → params.slug = undefined
// /shop/electronics → params.slug = ["electronics"]
// /shop/electronics/laptop → params.slug = ["electronics", "laptop"]
```

**Special files:**
- `page.tsx` → Makes route publicly accessible
- `layout.tsx` → Shared UI wrapper
- `loading.tsx` → Loading state
- `error.tsx` → Error boundary
- `not-found.tsx` → 404 page

**Folder Structure:**

```
app/
├── layout.tsx              (Root layout - global)
├── page.tsx                (Home page - /)
├── about/
│   └── page.tsx            (About page - /about)
└── blog/
    ├── layout.tsx          (Blog layout - sidebar)
    ├── page.tsx            (Blog list - /blog)
    └── [slug]/
        └── page.tsx        (Blog post - /blog/my-post)
```

**Root Layout:**

```tsx
